# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you
#   use pyenv and want other developers to use the same Python version
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a verified version, it can be committed.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally committed, but can be excluded.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally committed, but can be excluded.
#.pdm-python
#.pdm-build/

